<br>
I got baking up to 200 the hard way, and as a non-forager, too, bah.  Although I started baking from character inception, and most of my skills for a long while came as a part of natural hunting, after 135 I had to scurry, scrape, and beg for many different things.  Without my guild, I'd have never gotten beyond that point, and even then, I spent an inordinate amount of coin on mushrooms to get into the 190s.  Nowadays, I think a young baker could just sit in the little merchant hut in Jaggedpines and crank up to 191 in a few nights if they had enough seed money.  So it is frustrating, a bit, from that perspective.<br>
<br>
On the flip side, though, I'm glad I didn't bake before Luclin came out.  Luclin recipes, and the addition of *good* stats to baked foods, are a godsend.  Something I wanted to develop really just for character development ( and to avoid buying rations, heh, ) has actually turned out to turn a decent profit, at least since the bazaar came out and I can just sleep and sell things.<br>
<br>
All told, I'd rather have things this way than the old way of trying to dig up pixie dusts and dragon meat.  I'd have just had to give up by now if that was the case.<br>
